  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This retrospective study investigates surgical treatment of acetabular fractures in elderly
      patients (&gt;60 years of age), either undergoing joint-preserving surgery or joint-
      replacement. 1 year- outcome with regard to mobility and autonomy is assessed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
